items.name: Johnny Lawrence - [Cobra Kai / Karate Kid]
items.description:
Johnny Lawrence (played by actor: William Zabka in both "Cobra Kai" and the 1980's original movie "Karate Kid"). This is a high quality LoRA extracted from a Dreambooth trained checkpoint made w/ J.Penna's Dreambooth repo (trained locally).

The trigger works are "Johnnylawrence Person". Make sure you put "JohnnyLawrence Person" in your prompt alone w/ the usual LoRA filenaming.

For best results use Hires Fix. For ultimate results use in tandem w/ 30-60% the steps modified by Controlnet w/ Canny, Openpose, shuffle, reference, or Normal_bae (for example). This model was trained w/ a lot of steps so using a lower weight than "1" in the LoRA prompt (for example .8) will allow for more malleable image generations. Prompt weighting (()) can also help.

The samples were generated with V1.5 and also RealisitcVision 2.0. It should work with most models based off of V1.x of Stable Diffusion.

*SOME OF THE IMAGE SAMPLES WERE GENERATED W/ CONTROLNET - The site doesn't mention control net w/ the metadata on images. Someone dogged me w/ a 1 vote and F'U comment for being unable to replicate my results on previous model I uploaded. If you use the data a sample and don't get the same image generation it's likely because controlnet was used. You could always download the sample image and use -that- as a reference w/ a Controlnet model. Just play around).

items.name: Isometric Cutaway
items.description:
Isometric cutaway is a visual technique used in illustration and design to depict a three-dimensional object or space. It combines the isometric projection method with the concept of a cutaway, allowing viewers to see the internal structure or details of an object or building.

In an isometric cutaway illustration, the object or structure is depicted at an isometric angle, which means that the three principal axes (x, y, and z) are equally foreshortened. This creates a sense of depth and perspective while maintaining the accuracy of the object's proportions.

The cutaway aspect of the illustration involves removing a section or portion of the object to reveal its internal features or hidden details. This can be done by "slicing" the object along a specific plane or by selectively removing specific layers or sections to expose the inner workings or interior spaces.

Isometric cutaway illustrations are commonly used in technical and architectural drawings, product design, and visualizations of complex systems or machinery. They allow viewers to understand the internal structure or mechanisms of an object while maintaining a clear understanding of its external form.

This visual technique provides a unique perspective and can be especially useful when conveying complex information or explaining the functionality of a product or structure. It allows for a comprehensive view of an object's internal and external features in a single image, enhancing clarity and understanding for the viewer.

Isometric cutaway illustrations are a powerful tool for communicating information, providing an engaging and informative visual representation of an object or space's inner workings.

items.name: Sharpness Tweaker LoRA (锐度调整LoRA)
items.description:
特殊用法：

1. 你可以试着把权重设为负数（降锐化），然后拉高CFG Scale。这样效果可能要略好于直接锐化

2. 二次元模型一般不需要锐化，但可能会用到降锐化

【中文】

完全自由的锐度调节工具！

有3个版本，不过最推荐v3.0，因为它可以胜任的权重范围最广，但可能只有在高权重下才有明显效果

v3.0推荐权重：-2.0~2.0，权重越高，锐化就越强。负数则是使图像变平滑

【English】

A powerful sharpness tweaker!

There are 3 verisons for you to choose, but I suggest the v3.0 most since it is suitable for wide weight ranges (It may only work at high weights, however)

The recommend weight for v3.0 is -2.0~2.0. The higher the weight is, the sharper the images will be. If you set the weight to a negative number, it can make images smooth.

You can try to use negative weight and increase the CFG Scale, which may better than common way.

items.description:
Unlimited Blade Works (UBW) | Weapon LoCON


This is a LyCORIS and you need this Extension for this to work. Model changed from LoHA to LoCON in 1.6.

Weight can go from 0.5 up to 1.0. I recommend 0.9. ControlNet will streamline full body shots much easier, or more complex poses. Works with almost every Style, every Character and Photorealistic Models. I also recommend using some ControlNet Depth/HED for easier use. I personally dont use them, but every help is appreciated. Some of @antonio_riolo2610 Models: v1 / v2. Also a big thanks to @Temporarium for helping me out with the Dataset.

Refer to the version details for Changelog. Keep in mind, that despite this LoCON, that Weapons are very difficult to generate. This only helps, but dont solve the issue.

This is now an official release of this Model and includes 23 CONCEPTS. Trained on 6,5k Images with 16,5k Training Steps. Trained on 7k Images with 45k Training Steps. Some of these are still unstable, even going over every Image manually. I also included some stances and Weapons that can be combined (Dual Wield of Axe, etc). Try some crazy stuff, even I couldn't fully test this Model after many hours. Here are the Triggerwords and helping prompts:

TRIGGERS:

  • Axe²

  • BowAiming³

  • BowHolding³

  • DualWielding²

  • Fan²

  • KatanaOneHand

  • KatanaTwoHands³

  • Knife²

  • Kunai²³

  • Lightsaber²

  • Unlimited Blade Works²

  • MasterSword³

  • PlantedSword

  • Scythe

  • Sheathed

  • Shield²

  • Spear²

  • Staff

  • SwordAndSheath³

  • Tomahawk²

  • Trident²

  • Unsheathing³

  • Warhammer²

  • Whip

² = can be combined

³ = very unstable

Helping Prompt:

holding, weapon, holding weapon, holding (Triggertag)

Stances Prompt:

Weapon over shoulder, Weapon on back, fighting stance, stance

BETA RELEASES:

This is only a BETA. I will add more Swords, Weapons and Guns to this. SD doesn't like to generate Weapons (just like Ranni with 4 Arms). Trying to improve it on every Update. I recommend using these Settings: Sampling Method DPM++ SDE Karras with 30/40 Steps. If you know how to improve this, i'm happy to hear you out.

WARNING: This LoHA does have some problems and hits most of the time 1 out of 10 times. Hands are a big problem. Hand does not connect with the sword and sword does not appear in the right place sometimes. Unsheathing Sword is currently very unstable. Use pointy ears in Neg, if you are using Link Master Sword. Yor Knife gives normals knifes for some reason on my End.

Trigger Words:

Link Master Sword, Lightsaber, Dual Wielding Swords, One Handed Sword, Unsheathing Sword, Scythe, Sword and Shield, Staff, Trident, Planted Sword on Hand, Yor Knife, Unlimited Blade Works, Bow with Arrow.

I want to add these Concepts in the future as well:

Weapon Classes:

Axe, firearms, arc, Knife, hammer, rods, throwing stars, sickle, whips, guns, grenades, shields

Subcategories:

one-handed, Two handed, pistols, guns, machine guns, shotguns, grenade launcher, rocket launcher, sniper rifles, brass knuckles, throwing axes, spears, javelins, arrows, crossbows, Sling, sniper, bazooka, Foal

Variations:

warhammer, tomahawk, short sword, broadsword, rapiers, longsword, dagger, Kukri, katana, tanto, wakizashi, naginata, quarterstaff, war spear, double axe, hatchet, baton, Shield with integrated weapon, Dual wielding of other weapons

modelVersions.name: v2.0 (3.5)

Retrained the model. This time, there is some special sauce (Which I call crop augmentation).
Essentially, I ran the images through a model to get the saliency for each model and cropped them to a 1:1 ratio. In my initIal testing, square pictures are now much more defined and close up and the over quality appears to have improved. I described a bit of my process on twitter.
The epoch uploaded is epoch 4, which isn't the final epoch but is so far the best performing one.
N.B. the trigger word "notshaft style", doesn't strongly affect the image too much, I messed up and forgot to add keep tokens.
N.B 2: Consider letting the model stew a bit longer to get more the the fine details out (More steps. Euler a with 80 seems like a decent spot). Also, set the text encoder to 0.5. I'll probably find out how to properly train a text encoder eventually lol.
Hint: The examples are your friend. :3

items.name: Sentry Bot Voice (so-vits-svc model)
items.description:
I trained the singing voice clone AI on voice clips of the Sentry Bot from Fallout 4. I used the default training settings meaning 10000 epochs- though with the simplicity of the Sentry Bot's voice that was probably overkill...

Anyway, It works pretty well and the AI holds on to the "audio detail" of the Sentry Bot's voice, and where it messes up it still sounds believable (since the Sentry Bot's voice is already "noisy" and "imprecise" in a way). However, if you want those pitch changes found in the Sentry Bot's voice it needs to be included in the input audio. More on output quality, slow clear speaking is recommended for the input audio, since that's how the Sentry Bot speaks as its voice is hard to understand otherwise.

As per comment recommendations here is a link to a good repo that can run this model: https://github.com/voicepaw/so-vits-svc-fork

You can either install from source or use the pip commands that the README specifies

It has a GUI where you can specify the Weights, its associate config file, and the input audio you want to transform

If you can run Stable Diffusion then this AI should run fine under 5 minutes of input audio, where you need more vram for longer audios (though you can just cut up longer clips)

Here is the source:

Image source: https://www.nexusmods.com/fallout4/mods/56150

items.description:
‼ IMPORTANT ‼

  • Your voice matters! Show your support and leave a post, comment and most importantly a review! ⭐

  • Custom LORAs available upon request. Just buymeacoffee.☕

  • This is now a + LORA! (details in workflow advice below) 👇(workflow advice below) 👇

📝Biography📝

🌟Aya Beshen🌟

also known by various aliases such as Alina Goldman, Alina R, and Elin, is a Ukrainian adult model. She was born on October 22, 1995, in Kyiv, Ukraine, and is currently 27 years old. Aya stands at a height of 5'10" (177 cm) and weighs around 112 lbs (51 kg). She has a slim body type with measurements of 35-22-35 and a bra size of 36D (80D). Aya has natural brown hair, brown eyes, and no tattoos or piercings.

Aya began her modeling career in 2013 at the age of 18 and was active in the industry for around six years until 2019. During her career, she modeled for various premium studio sites such as HEGRE-ART, PHOTODROMM, METART, etc. Aya was known for her all-natural body and her passion for posing in artistic and glamour shoots. She also enjoyed traveling, participating in sports such as swimming, dance, and arts.

Currently, there is no information available on Aya's whereabouts or what she is doing now. However, her career as an adult model has left a lasting impression on her fans. Aya's beauty, confidence, and captivating personality made her a favorite among her admirers. She will be remembered as a talented model who embraced her sexuality and expressed it through her work in the industry.

💡Workflow Advice💡

🔧Prompt and Sampling🔧

  • What's the + for?

    • Just an easy way to indicate the dataset image for this particular LORA was based off a minimum of 1024px+ quality source images with the LORA trained at 1024,1024 (I may go higher in the future if I can get a properly working configuration).

    • For the most part, you can start with higher base resolutions to capture more details and/or generate higher quality outputs. See some of the gallery examples.

    • You don't have to gen at high resolution, low res generations will be better quality as well.

  • Most images have been generated with LORA weighted @ .75 - 1.1.

  • For photoreal shots, I've found sampling steps best well above 50 give better results.

  • ControlNet is your friend. Embrace the dark side.😈

    • Tile pre-sample and model is good for extreme close ups

    • I use segmentation for lots of my generations now.

🚀Upscaling🚀

  • Try the Ultimate SD upscale script!

  • Sometimes I just send it to Ultimate SD upscale after a quick render and run 2x at a scale of two.

  • Ultimate SD upscale script used @ ~.15 - .4 denoising using 8x NMKD Faces or 4X UltraSharp redraw upscalers.

🗒️Side Notes🗒️

  • This + series is something new, let me know if I should take the extra time it takes to create these type of LoRAs or just stick with the regular quality.

  • Help me help you: Leave a review if you've used this LORA.

  • Most of my gens are not voodoo or outside of workflows I've indicated here or in my other posts.

    • In other words: Leave a comment if you are having issues getting good output, I'll try to respond with suggestions.

A commission of @Zorglub.

Shohreh Aghdashloo is an Iranian/American actress, mainly known for her role in the sci-fi TV show The Expanse.

Updated: Apologies for the quick update, but I misjudged step 1200 at first and it seems actually better than the previous version. :)

1200-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images with my usual settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (sh0hreh:0.99), a woman, closeup zoomed in tight crop portrait, sitting at a (table on a seaside boardwalk cafe bar drinks cocktails:1.2) wearing a (sexy sweater off-shoulders:1.3) (drinks on table:1.3) (Lighting-Gold:1.2) foreground objects background details (masterpiece:1.2) (photorealistic:1.2) (bokeh:1.2) (best quality) (color grading) (detailed skin:1.3) (intricate) (8k) (HDR) (cinematic lighting:1.3) (sharp focus)"

items.name: Ivan Bilibin Style
items.description:
Ivan Bilibin was a Russian illustrator and artist known for his distinctive and enchanting illustrations, particularly for Russian folktales and fairy tales.

His style can be described as romantic, nostalgic, and heavily influenced by Russian folklore and traditional art. Bilibin's illustrations often feature intricate patterns, bold colors, and stylized figures reminiscent of traditional Russian folk art.

He had a remarkable ability to capture the essence of Russian fairy tales and folklore, bringing the stories to life through his intricate and evocative illustrations. Bilibin's artwork often depicted mythical creatures, heroic figures, and enchanting landscapes, transporting viewers into a world of magic and wonder.

His illustrations were not only aesthetically captivating but also served as a way to preserve and promote Russian cultural heritage. Bilibin's dedication to folklore and his desire to revive traditional Russian art forms made him a prominent figure in the Russian art scene.

In addition to his illustrations for fairy tales, Bilibin also created artwork for books, magazines, and theater productions. His intricate and imaginative designs brought a touch of magic and beauty to these various mediums.

Bilibin's illustrations continue to captivate audiences, as they evoke a sense of nostalgia, enchantment, and a connection to Russian cultural identity. His artistic legacy has had a lasting impact, influencing subsequent generations of illustrators and keeping the rich tradition of Russian folklore alive through his beautiful and timeless artwork.
